<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n25118h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n25" href="#n25118h">N25 (VI.B.15)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n25all.htm#n25118h"> 118(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> read bible to a cow</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">A medi&aelig;val remedy for removing grit from the eye was to chant the psalm &lsquo;Qui habitat&rsquo; three times over water, with which the eye was then to be douched, while modern Welsh folk-lore tells of the farmer who, <mark>having a cow sick</mark> on a Sunday, gave her physic, and then, fearing that she was dying, ran into the house to <mark>fetch a Bible and read a chapter to her</mark>. <small> Edward Clodd, <a name="ECTTT" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ECTTT"><cite title="source">Tom Tit Tot</cite></a> (1898) 222-3</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c14072k" href="c14all.htm#c14072k">VI.C.14:072(k)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
